      >
        Measure roof pitch, joint angles, and slopes instantly — from a photo or your webcam. No app, no signup, no ads.
      </p>

      <!-- Main Action Buttons -->
      <div
        class="mt-4 sm:mt-6 flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 w-full max-w-md mx-auto px-3 select-none"
      >
        <a
          href="#angle-meter"
          class="group w-full sm:w-60 inline-flex h-12 sm:h-14 items-center justify-center gap-2 sm:gap-3 rounded-xl bg-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white dark:bg-white dark:hover:bg-neutral-100 dark:text-neutral-950 px-6 sm:px-10 font-sans text-sm sm:text-base font-bold shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 ease-out transform hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <Compass class="h-5 w-5 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300" />
          <span>Measure Now</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/tool/webcam"
          class="group w-full sm:w-60 inline-flex h-12 sm:h-14 items-center justify-center gap-2 sm:gap-3 rounded-xl border-2 border-neutral-900 bg-transparent text-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-100 dark:border-white dark:text-white dark:hover:bg-white/10 px-6 sm:px-10 font-sans text-sm sm:text-base font-bold transition-all duration-300 ease-out transform hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <Camera class="h-5 w-5 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300" />
          <span>Use Camera</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Feature Pills Section (with Why Choose label and light gray bg block) -->
      <div class="mt-6 sm:mt-8 bg-[#F5F5F5] dark:bg-white/[0.04] p-4 sm:p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-100 dark:border-transparent max-w-xl w-full mx-auto text-center shadow-sm">
        <p class="font-sans text-[11px] tracking-[0.1em] text-[#888888] dark:text-[#6B7280] font-semibold uppercase mb-3">WHY IT'S DIFFERENT</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#ebebeb] bg-white text-[#888888] font-mono text-[10px] sm:text-xs shadow-sm whitespace-nowrap dark:bg-white/[0.02] dark:border-white/10 dark:text-slate-300"
          >
            High Precision Scale
          </span>
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#ebebeb] bg-white text-[#888888] font-mono text-[10px] sm:text-xs shadow-sm whitespace-nowrap dark:bg-white/[0.02] dark:border-white/10 dark:text-slate-300"
          >
            Zero Server Traffic
          </span>
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#ebebeb] bg-white text-[#888888] font-mono text-[10px] sm:text-xs shadow-sm whitespace-nowrap dark:bg-white/[0.02] dark:border-white/10 dark:text-slate-300"
          >
            Live Video Framing
          </span>
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#ebebeb] bg-white text-[#888888] font-mono text-[10px] sm:text-xs shadow-sm whitespace-nowrap dark:bg-white/[0.02] dark:border-white/10 dark:text-slate-300"
          >
            Client-Side Security
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interactive Angle Meter Tool Section -->
  <section class="pb-16 sm:pb-20 bg-[#fafafa]" id="angle-meter">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-6 sm:mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-sans text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[#171717]">
          Interactive Measure Workspace
        </h2>
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-[#888888] mt-1">
          Reposition the handles along the fixed perimeter dial to analyze
          custom angles
        </p>
      </div>
      <ImageAngleFinder />
    </div>
  </section>



  <!-- Core Features / Pillars -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white border-y border-[#ebebeb] relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
        <h2
          class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#0070f3]"
        >
          Engineered Design System
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mt-3 font-sans text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-1px] text-[#171717]"
        >
          Built for high-contrast visibility and total security.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-6 lg:gap-8">
        <!-- Feature 1 -->
        <div
          class="group flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa] hover:bg-white hover:border-[#0070f3]/30 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 ease-out transform hover:-translate-y-1"
        >
          <div
            class="h-10 w-10 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-white group-hover:bg-[#0070f3] text-[#0070f3] group-hover:text-white border border-[#ebebeb] group-hover:border-[#0070f3] shadow-vercel-1 transition-all duration-300 ease-out"
          >
            <Shield class="h-5 w-5" />
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-sans text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold text-[#171717]">
            Sandboxed Client Operations
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            All calculations and image parses execute locally within your
            browser sandbox. Your camera streams and images are never sent to
            external servers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 2 -->
        <div
          class="group flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa] hover:bg-white hover:border-[#0070f3]/30 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 ease-out transform hover:-translate-y-1"
        >
          <div
            class="h-10 w-10 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-white group-hover:bg-[#0070f3] text-[#0070f3] group-hover:text-white border border-[#ebebeb] group-hover:border-[#0070f3] shadow-vercel-1 transition-all duration-300 ease-out"
          >
            <Zap class="h-5 w-5" />
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-sans text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold text-[#171717]">
            Zero Interface Blockers
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            Our clean workspace avoids distracting ads, banner blocks, and
            cookies. We offer a dedicated developer-grade canvas designed for
            concentration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 3 -->
        <div
          class="group flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa] hover:bg-white hover:border-[#0070f3]/30 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 ease-out transform hover:-translate-y-1"
        >
          <div
            class="h-10 w-10 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-white group-hover:bg-[#0070f3] text-[#0070f3] group-hover:text-white border border-[#ebebeb] group-hover:border-[#0070f3] shadow-vercel-1 transition-all duration-300 ease-out"
          >
            <Cpu class="h-5 w-5" />
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-sans text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold text-[#171717]">
            Freeze-Frame Stabilization
          </h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            Eliminate camera shake and alignment challenges. Take a quick static
            snapshot of the live webcam feed to align measurements with
            accuracy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Competitor Weakness Comparison Chart -->
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20 bg-[#fafafa]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-3 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-8 sm:mb-12">
        <h2
          class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#0070f3]"
        >
          Technical Auditing
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mt-3 font-sans text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.8px] text-[#171717]"
        >
          Comparing architectural approaches
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="bg-white border border-[#ebebeb] rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-vercel-3"
      >
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table
          class="w-full text-left font-sans text-sm divide-y divide-[#ebebeb]"
        >
          <thead
            class="bg-[#fafafa] font-mono text-[10px] sm:text-xs text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-wider"
          >
            <tr>
              <th class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-semibold border-b border-[#ebebeb] whitespace-nowrap"
                >Workspace Capabilities</th
              >
              <th class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-semibold border-b border-[#ebebeb] whitespace-nowrap text-center"
                >This Platform</th
              >
              <th class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-semibold border-b border-[#ebebeb] whitespace-nowrap text-center"
                >Legacy Alternatives</th
              >
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#ebebeb]">
            {
              comparisonData.map((row) => (
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-sans text-xs sm:text-[13.5px] text-[#171717] font-medium">
                    {row.feature}
                  </td>
                  <td class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-sans text-xs sm:text-[13.5px] text-center">
                    {typeof row.us === "boolean" ? (
                      <span class="inline-flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-blue-50 text-[#0070f3] border border-blue-200">
                        <Check class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
                      </span>
                    ) : (
                      <span class="text-[#0070f3] font-semibold">{row.us}</span>
                    )}
                  </td>
                  <td class="px-3 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-4 font-sans text-xs sm:text-[13.5px] text-[#888888] text-center">
                    {typeof row.them === "boolean" ? (
                      <span class="inline-flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rose-50 text-rose-500 border border-rose-200">
                        <X class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
                      </span>
                    ) : (
                      <span>{row.them}</span>
                    )}
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))
            }
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- User Segments Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
        <h2
          class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#0070f3]"
        >
          Target Contexts
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mt-3 font-sans text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-1px] text-[#171717]"
        >
          Engineered for builders, architects, and designers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
        <!-- Woodworkers -->
        <a
          href="/woodworking-angle-finder"
          class="group flex flex-col justify-between p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa] hover:bg-white transition-colors"
        >
          <div>
            <h3
              class="font-sans text-base font-semibold text-[#171717]"
            >
              Woodworking & Joinery
            </h3>
          <p
            class="mt-3 sm:mt-3.5 font-sans text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed"
          >
              Verify custom miter cut values, compound angles, and trim
              installations. Support polygon shapes like octagons and hexagons
              in real time.
            </p>
          </div>
          <span
            class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase text-[#0070f3] group-hover:underline"
          >
            Joinery Guide <ArrowRight class="h-3 w-3" />
          </span>
        </a>

        <!-- Roofers -->
        <a
          href="/roof-pitch-calculator"
          class="group flex flex-col justify-between p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa] hover:bg-white transition-colors"
        >
          <div>
            <h3
              class="font-sans text-base font-semibold text-[#171717]"
            >
              Architectural Slopes
            </h3>
            <p
              class="mt-3.5 font-sans text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed"
            >
              Measure steepness, roof pitches, and stair grades directly from
              pictures. Instantly convert slope degrees to standard pitch
              ratios.
            </p>
          </div>
          <span
            class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase text-[#0070f3] group-hover:underline"
          >
            Slope Calc <ArrowRight class="h-3 w-3" />
          </span>
        </a>

        <!-- Students -->
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa]"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-base font-semibold text-[#171717]">
              Academic Geometry
            </h3>
            <p
              class="mt-3.5 font-sans text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed"
            >
              Verify geometry formulas, math worksheets, and blueprint angles on
              a clean browser-based digital grid.
            </p>
          </div>
          <span
            class="mt-5 font-mono text-[9px] uppercase text-[#888888] tracking-wider"
            >No installation needed</span
          >
        </div>

        <!-- DIY / Designers -->
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] bg-[#fafafa]"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-base font-semibold text-[#171717]">
              Interior & CAD Drafting
            </h3>
            <p
              class="mt-3.5 font-sans text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed"
            >
              Plan room configurations, verify photographic grids, check
              perspective lines, and inspect scale layouts from standard image
              formats.
            </p>
          </div>
          <span
            class="mt-5 font-mono text-[9px] uppercase text-[#888888] tracking-wider"
            >Runs offline locally</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Protractor Guide Section (SEO Keywords Optimized) -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]" id="guide">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#0070f3]">
          Educational Resource
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-1px] text-[#171717]">
          Protractor & Angle Measurement Guide
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 sm:gap-12">
        <!-- Main Content (8 Columns on Large Screens) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-8">
          
          <!-- Section 1: Definition -->
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-[#171717] mb-3">
              What is a Protractor? (Protractor Definition)
            </h3>
            <p class="font-sans text-sm sm:text-base text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
              A <strong>protractor</strong> is a specialized measurement tool used to measure angles. According to the standard <strong>protractor definition</strong>, it is typically a circular or semicircular instrument graduated in angular degrees (usually from 0° to 180° or 360°). Traditional protractors are mechanical tools made of transparent plastic, wood, or metal. However, modern tasks often require a <strong>digital protractor</strong> or an <strong>online protractor tool</strong> to analyze digital screens, photographs, blueprints, or camera views with high precision.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- Section 2: How to Use -->
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-[#171717] mb-3">
              How to Use a Protractor to Measure Angles
            </h3>
            <p class="font-sans text-sm sm:text-base text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Understanding <strong>how to use a protractor</strong> is essential for mathematics, geometry projects, and technical drafting. Whether you are using a mechanical, digital, or <strong>protractor online</strong> utility, the core process of <strong>measuring angles with a protractor</strong> remains similar:
            </p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 font-sans text-sm sm:text-base text-[#4d4d4d] space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>Identify the Vertex:</strong> Find the point (vertex) where the two lines forming the angle meet. Place the center mark of the protractor tool directly on this vertex.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Align the Baseline:</strong> Rotate the protractor so that the zero-degree baseline line aligns perfectly with one of the angle's rays (or arms).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Read the Measurement:</strong> Trace the second ray of the angle to where it crosses the curved degree markings on the protractor scale. If your angle opens from the right side, read the inner scale; if it opens from the left side, read the outer scale.
              </li>
            </ol>
            <p class="font-sans text-sm sm:text-base text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mt-4">
              On our digital tool, <strong>how to use protractor</strong> actions are simplified: just upload your photo, place the digital vertex handle directly on the angle vertex, and align the two adjustable arms along the edges of the shape to read the precise degrees instantly.
