            <p class="font-sans text-sm sm:text-base text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
              In geometry and architectural drafting, the <strong>protractor and compass</strong> are historical partner tools. While the protractor measures and lays out angles, the compass is used to draw clean circles, construct geometric arcs, and bisect angles. By mastering both tools, students, woodworkers, and designers can construct complex shapes, blueprints, and joints with exact mathematical ratios.
